        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName><hi rend="print">Down.</hi> | Beckenham | <hi rend="print">Kent. S.E.</hi></placeName>
                    <date>Mar 5<hi rend="superscript">th</hi>.</date>
                    <salute>My dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>I am very much obliged to you for your letter and for the great trouble you have taken in copying extracts from Hyrtl’s work.<ref target="#foot.f2"/> The facts are curious and would have been particularly useful to me when writing my book on Variation under Domestication.<ref target="#foot.f3"/> None of the facts given by Hyrtl are so interesting as your case of the De Haas family.<ref target="#foot.f4"/> Thank you much for telling me about M<hi rend="superscript">lle</hi>. Cl. Royer, as I shall be able to put a foot-note in the French edit. on your authority.<ref target="#foot.f5"/> You express yourself very well in English and know the language almost perfectly; but I am inclined to think that it is a correct English expression to speak of all the descendants from any one man as the line of descent.<ref target="#foot.f6"/> In a week or two time, when my book is reprinted I shall have great pleasure in sending you a copy.<ref target="#foot.f7"/></p>
<p>Believe me My dear sir | Yours sincerely | Ch. Darwin</p>
<p>PS It will be superfluous in your publisher to send me <hi rend="doubleUnderline">two</hi> copies of the Dutch translation though I am much obliged for the offer.<ref target="#foot.f8"/></p> 
                </div>
            </div>

            
        </div>

        

        

        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">The year is established by the relationship between this letter and the <ref target="./DCP-LETT-7533.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter from Hermanus Hartogh Heijs van Zouteveen, 2 March 1871</ref>.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">See <ref target="./DCP-LETT-7533.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter from Hermanus Hartogh Heijs van Zouteveen, 2 March 1871</ref>. CD refers to Joseph Hyrtl, <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_4078.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Hyrtl 1847</ref>, and <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_4079.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Hyrtl 1865</ref>.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f3"><ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_7951.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Variation</hi></ref>.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f4">See <ref target="./DCP-LETT-7533.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter from Hermanus Hartogh Heijs van Zouteveen, 2 March 1871</ref> and n. 24.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f5">See <ref target="./DCP-LETT-7533.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter from Hermanus Hartogh Heijs van Zouteveen, 2 March 1871</ref> and n. 23. CD refers to <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_4113.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Clémence Auguste Royer</ref>. CD did not add a reference to <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_6767.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Royer 1870</ref> in the French edition of <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_1966.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Descent</hi></ref> (Moulinié trans. 1872), but did refer to it in <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_1967.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Descent</hi> 2d ed.</ref>, p. 163 n. 31.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f6">See <ref target="./DCP-LETT-7533.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter from Hermanus Hartogh Heijs van Zouteveen, 2 March 1871</ref> and n. 29.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f7">In his letter of 2 March 1871, <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_2155.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Hermanus Hartogh Heijs van Zouteveen</ref> asked CD for a signed copy of <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_1966.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Descent</hi></ref>. The second printing of <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_1966.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Descent</hi></ref> was made in March 1871 (<ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_2661.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Freeman 1977</ref>).</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f8">See <ref target="./DCP-LETT-7533.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter from Hermanus Hartogh Heijs van Zouteveen, 2 March 1871</ref> and n. 1.</note>
